[Name] Libx86
[Summary] A hardware-independent library for executing real-mode x86 code
[Description] Libx86 provides an interface, lrmi, to make it easy to
make real-mode x86 BIOS calls from userland on x86 machines. It will
also run on platforms such as amd64 and alpha, where it uses x86emu to
execute lrmi function calls.
